I have a question about the mechanics of wildcard matching.
The example below assumes that we are using the authoritative server for the
com domain.

We have a name server here that, when looking for a MX record for
a.b.c.com, it tries in order:

	a.b.c.com
	*.b.c.com
	*.*.c.com
	*.*.*.com

Is this the correct technique? Or should it be

	a.b.c.com
	*.b.c.com
	*.c.com
	*.com

We are trying to get an internal nameserver forward to our external
nameserver. The internal machine is not a Unix machine.
Do we have a configuration problem, or is the name server buggy?

